text: The Economical Rice is priced above average compared to other stores near the vicinity. The food portion is decent. Most important the Aunty served food with a smile and had no problems at all. Not a bad place at all if you are hungry and want to stop and eat for awhile. The area is clean and not really dirty.

Food is not bad here and best is air conditioned. Had the bee hoon soto, chilli is good! You tiao also crispy and hot, they sell dessert too at this shop!
Chicken rice not bad too..

I reckon they are closed for good.
Just want try my luck for knowing the new address for Malay rice as I really like their food a lot ðŸ˜­
The beehoon at the Economic Beehoon stall (halal side) tastes SO GOOD I can eat it plain.

Good food, especially the Malay stall.
Anyone knows if they would be relocated nearby?
